			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2022</a> paper:</span><br><i>Property-Based Testing: Climbing the Stairway to Verification</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/ZilinChen.html">Zilin Chen</a>, <a href="../profile/ChristineRizkallah.html">Christine Rizkallah</a>, <a href="../profile/LiamOConnor.html">Liam O’Connor</a>, <a href="../profile/ParthaSusarla.html">Partha Susarla</a>, <a href="../profile/GerwinKlein.html">Gerwin Klein</a>, <a href="../profile/GernotHeiser.html">Gernot Heiser</a>, <a href="../profile/GabrieleKeller.html">Gabriele Keller</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/3567512.3567520">10.1145/3567512.3567520</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5c.html"><span class="tagM">T5C: Testing</span></a><ul><li> It advances property-based testing techniques and their role in verification workflows.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5d.html"><span class="tagL">T5D: Formal Methods</span></a><ul><li> It connects testing results to stronger formal verification goals (proof/verification support).
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t6d.html"><span class="tagL">T6D: Synergies</span></a><ul><li> It bridges methods from testing and verification, highlighting their synergy.
</li></ul></li></ul>
